        <ontology:took_place_at rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/phenomenal_place/49.0_20.0"/>
        <ontology:hasDescription>The MOVING reference member state of this VC (Value Chain) is SLOVAKIA. The reference MOVING Card ID of this VC is VC 18 SK. Key activities: packaging and marketing. Key actors: producers, actors in marketing. Labelling: waters with a certain amount of minerals can be labeled as &amp;apos;mineral water&amp;apos;.  </ontology:hasDescription>
    </NamedIndividual>
    


    <!-- https://dlnarratives.eu/narrative/N323_VC_18_SK/event/ev10 -->


    <NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://dlnarratives.eu/narrative/N323_VC_18_SK/event/ev10">
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/event-type/valorisation_event"/>
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/ontology#Event"/>
        <ontology:hasEntity rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/resource/Q11042"/>
        <ontology:hasEntity rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/resource/Q38112"/>
        <ontology:hasEntity rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/resource/Q43619"/>
        <ontology:hasEntity rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/resource/Q576355"/>
        <ontology:hasEntity rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/resource/Q646107"/>
        <ontology:hasEntity rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/resource/Q7777019"/>
        <ontology:isPresentedBefore rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/narrative/N323_VC_18_SK/event/ev11"/>
        <ontology:is_identified_by rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/appellation/Innovation"/>
        <ontology:partOfNarrative rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/narrative/N323_VC_18_SK"/>
        <ontology:took_place_at rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/phenomenal_place/48.924427299820955_19.258941446074985"/>
        <ontology:took_place_at rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/place/1"/>
        <ontology:hasDescription>The type of innovation of this VC (Value Chain) is Endogenous. Innovative is the mixture of local resources - water and local wild herbs. The innovation is related to New processes and New marketing strategies. The land use systems involved are Forestry, Natural land and Meadows with wild herbs. The local assets include Natural and cultural.  </ontology:hasDescription>
    </NamedIndividual>
    


    <!-- https://dlnarratives.eu/narrative/N323_VC_18_SK/event/ev11 -->


    <NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://dlnarratives.eu/narrative/N323_VC_18_SK/event/ev11">
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/event-type/valorisation_event"/>
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/ontology#Event"/>
        <ontology:hasEntity rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/resource/Q1365924"/>
        <ontology:hasEntity rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/resource/Q193083"/>
        <ontology:hasEntity rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/resource/Q214"/>
        <ontology:hasEntity rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/resource/Q3554446"/>
        <ontology:is_identified_by rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/appellation/Concluding_remarks"/>
        <ontology:partOfNarrative rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/narrative/N323_VC_18_SK"/>
        <ontology:took_place_at rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/phenomenal_place/49.0_20.0"/>
        <ontology:hasDescription>Slovakia is in number and quality of mineral springs among the richest countries in the world. VC is present in all mountain NUTS3 in Slovakia: SK 022, SK 031, SK 032, SK 041, SK 042.  </ontology:hasDescription>
    </NamedIndividual>
    


    <!-- https://dlnarratives.eu/narrative/N323_VC_18_SK/event/ev2 -->


    <NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://dlnarratives.eu/narrative/N323_VC_18_SK/event/ev2">
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/event-type/natural_event"/>
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/event-type/valorisation_event"/>
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/ontology#Event"/>
        <ontology:hasEntity rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/resource/Q1186992"/>
        <ontology:hasEntity rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/resource/Q12014035"/>
        <ontology:hasEntity rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/resource/Q1265417"/>
        <ontology:hasEntity rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/resource/Q1288"/>
        <ontology:hasEntity rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/resource/Q1767601"/>
        <ontology:hasEntity rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/resource/Q178921"/>
        <ontology:hasEntity rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/resource/Q214"/>
        <ontology:hasEntity rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/resource/Q4946461"/>
        <ontology:hasEntity rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/resource/Q53121"/>
        <ontology:isPresentedBefore rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/narrative/N323_VC_18_SK/event/ev3"/>
        <ontology:is_identified_by rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/appellation/Mountain_landscape_and_reference_chains"/>
        <ontology:partOfNarrative rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/narrative/N323_VC_18_SK"/>
        <ontology:took_place_at rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/phenomenal_place/48.950719444_19.262488888"/>
        <ontology:took_place_at rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/place/0"/>
        <ontology:hasDescription>The reference mountain chain of this VC is Slovak Carpathians. The reference mountain landscape of this VC is Liptovská osada. VC is present in all mountain NUTS3 in Slovakia (row57). A part of the LAU2 Liptovská osada, where the mineral spring is located, is part of the National Parc Nízke Tatry. The mineral water was in the past also used for the bath therapies in the spa area. The village has numerous accommodation facilities for visitors, some of which are provided in private houses. The local landscape also has numerous hiking and biking trails.  </ontology:hasDescription>
    </NamedIndividual>
    


